# Generated run artifacts are NOT committed — each harness run writes a new
# timestamped report/log here. Two example sets are tracked deliberately:
#   * the 20260617T182214Z-* trio — the llama validation harness --mock reference;
#   * the SYNTHETIC-SAMPLE-* pair — the Grok harness offline self-test reference
#     (reproducible via `python -m grok.cli --self-test --emit-sample`).
# Everything else is ignored so real runs never clutter the tree. Real Grok runs
# are stamped with a wall-clock run id and stay ignored (and unlabelled-real
# reports must never be committed — they would be unverified by definition).
*
!.gitignore
!20260617T182214Z-report.json
!20260617T182214Z-report.txt
!20260617T182214Z.log
!SYNTHETIC-SAMPLE-grok-4.3-self-test.json
!SYNTHETIC-SAMPLE-comparison.md
